{"title_page": "Motivation (Normani song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 single by Normani}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Motivation\n| cover      = Normani - Motivation.png\n| alt        =A young black woman looks at the camera while sitting on a floor against a pink background.\n| artist     = [[Normani]]\n| type       = single\n| album      = \n| released   = {{start date|mf=yes|2019|8|16}}\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n* [[radio]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = <!--Do not add unsourced genres -->\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/126038/normani-pays-tribute-to-britney-and-beyonce-in-motivation-music-video/|title=Normani pays tribute to Britney and Beyonc\u00e9 in Motivation music video|website=[[Gay Times]]|first=Sam|last=Damshenas|date=August 16, 2019|accessdate=August 17, 2019}}</ref><!--Pop is sourced in Reception section-->\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=13}}\n| label      =\n* [[Keep Cool Records|Keep Cool]]\n* [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Savan Kotecha]]\n* [[Ariana Grande]]\n* [[Max Martin]]\n* [[Normani|Normani Kordei Hamilton]]\n* [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]]\n| producer   =\n* Ilya\n| prev_title = [[Dancing with a Stranger]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[Diamonds (Megan Thee Stallion & Normani song)|Diamonds]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|FKXSh14svlQ|\"Motivation\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Motivation'''\" is a song by American singer [[Normani]], released on August 16, 2019. The song was written by [[Ariana Grande]], [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]], [[Max Martin]], Normani, [[Savan Kotecha]], and produced by Ilya.<!--Do not speculate that it is the second single from her debut album without a source.--> It reached the top 40 in ten countries including the US and UK.  The music video was released the same day as the song, it was directed by [[Dave Meyers (director)|Dave Meyers]]. It will be included on her upcoming debut solo album, which is expected to be released in 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.capitalfm.com/news/normani-debut-album-2020-release-date-motivation/|title=Normani Confirms 14 Track Debut Album Is 'Halfway Done' & Will Drop In 2020|website=Capital|language=en|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> The song was ranked as one of the best song of 2019 by various publications,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/music/g25833832/best-new-songs-2019/|title=These 19 New Songs Are the Best Bangers of 2019|last=Chambers|first=Hannah|last2=Baker|first2=Emma|date=2019-11-20|website=Cosmopolitan|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popbuzz.com/music/features/best-singles-2019-songs-of-the-year/|title=The 20 best singles of 2019|website=PopBuzz|language=en|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> and was listed as the 79th greatest song of the 2010s by [[Crack Magazine]].\n\n==Background and release==\n\"Motivation\" was initially teased with a snippet by Normani on her Twitter on August 2, 2019.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1157369824621793280|title=\u2728\ud83d\udda4\ud83c\udfb6|user=[[Normani]]|date=August 2, 2019|accessdate=August 9, 2019}}</ref> She further spoke on the song, as well as Ariana Grande's involvement in co-writing, during ''[[Rolling Stone]]''{{'}}s Morning Sessions at [[Lollapalooza]], explaining \"[Grande]'s dope. She also has a part in the record that I'm releasing, too. She wrote on it.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/ariana-grande-feature-normani-next-single-869177/|title=Normani Reveals Ariana Grande Wrote on Her New Single|last=Holmes|first=Charles|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=August 8, 2019|accessdate=August 9, 2019}}</ref> The song was officially announced on August 9 and released on August 16, 2019.<ref name=\"!!!\" >{{cite tweet|user=Normani|number=1159904368151453696|title=8/16/19 !!!!!|date=August 9, 2019|accessdate=August 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\n\n===Synopsis===\nA music video was released \nalongside the song on August 16, and was directed by [[Dave Meyers (director)|Dave Meyers]] and Daniel Russell.<ref name=\"Rap-Up\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rap-up.com/2019/08/15/video-normani-motivation/|title=Watch Normani's Throwback Video for 'Motivation'|work=[[Rap-Up]]|date=August 16, 2019|accessdate=August 16, 2019}}</ref> It features homages to music videos from the late 1990s and early 2000s, such as \"[[Goodies (song)|Goodies]]\" by [[Ciara]], \"[[Crazy in Love]]\" by [[Beyonc\u00e9]], \"[[...Baby One More Time (song)|...Baby One More Time]]\" by [[Britney Spears]] and \"[[I'm Real (Jennifer Lopez song)#Murder remix|I'm Real (Remix)]]\" by [[Jennifer Lopez]] and [[Ja Rule]].<ref name=\"Rap-Up\"/> The location of the video is in the same Los Angeles, Boyle Heights, neighborhood and park (Pecan Park) of Lopez and Ja Rule's \"I'm Real\" video.\n\nThe video begins with a younger version of Normani watching the [[BET]] music video countdown show ''[[106 & Park]]'' and daydreaming that former hosts [[Terrence J]] and [[Rocsi Diaz]] announced that she has the \"number 1 video in the world\", while her grandmother in the background tells her to lower the noise but then gives her blessing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3135414/normani-motivation-video/|title=Normani's 'Motivation' Is A Rain-Soaked Spectacle That Beyonc\u00e9 Would Be Proud Of|website=MTV}}</ref> As \"Motivation\" starts to play, it transitions from the living room to the screen where she is seen walking in the middle of a road, inspired by Beyonc\u00e9's \"[[Crazy in Love]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rap-up.com/2019/08/15/video-normani-motivation/|title=Watch Normani's Throwback Video for 'Motivation'|website=Rap-Up}}</ref> The second sequence is a dance sequence, with Normani dancing with her dancers in a [[Los Angeles]] neighborhood. The scene shifts to a fence background where Normani is seen climbing the fence while dancing before moving to a basketball court where she performs a [[gymnastics]] tumbling pass and a basketball technique. The rain sequence is then shown where Normani is accompanied by a band. The video ends as Normani performs a final dance routine in the late afternoon.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8527576/normani-motivation-music-video|title=Normani's 'Motivation' Video Is Loaded With Throwback Moments|website=Billboard}}</ref>\n\n===Recognition===\nUpon the release the music video for \u201cMotivation\u201d went viral due to the video\u2019s intense choreography, more specifically a basketball move that started a viral dance challenge.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/av/newsbeat-49449275/motivation-challenge-fans-attempt-normani-s-basketball-trick|title=Fans attempt Normani's Motivation challenge|website=BBC News|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2019/08/21/normanis-insane-motivation-dance-move-launches-viral-butt-challenge/|title=Normani\u2019s insane \u2018Motivation\u2019 dance move launches viral butt challenge|last=Steussy|first=Lauren|date=2019-08-21|website=New York Post|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> The music video received acclaim from music critics and was widespread across social media from many celebrities in support of the song, including [[Ariana Grande]], [[Kehlani]], [[Lizzo]], [[Halsey (singer)|Halsey]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8527584/normani-motivation-video-celebrity-reaction|title=Ariana Grande, Kehlani, Lizzo, Halsey & Charlie Puth Can't Get Enough of Normani's 'Motivation' Video|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> [[Cardi B]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2019/08/16/normani-reacts-cardi-b-compliment-motivation-music-video-instagram-post/|title=Normani Freaks Out After Cardi B Shares Clip Of Her Twerking In \u2018Motivation\u2019 Video: \u2018I\u2019m Overwhelmed\u2019|last=Shilliday|first=Beth|date=2019-08-17|website=Hollywood Life|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> and [[Kelly Clarkson]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/kelly-clarkson-normani-the-voice|title=Kelly Clarkson Attempted Normani's Basketball Trick for a Very Special Reason|last=Gemmill|first=Allie|website=Teen Vogue|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> ''Siobhan Burke'' of ''[[The New York Times]]'' wrote \u201cTwerking on a chain-link fence; doing a split on concrete in the rain; bouncing a basketball off multiple body parts, between effortless pirouettes: When Normani released the music video for her irresistible single \u201cMotivation\u201d in August, the message was clear. Not only could she sing \u2014 she could also really, really dance.\u201d<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/03/arts/dance/normani-motivation-dance.html|title=Normani Talks \u2018Motivation\u2019: \u2018Dance Was My First Passion\u2019|last=Burke|first=Siobhan|date=2019-09-03|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-01-08|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> ''Tom Breihan'' for [[Stereogum]] wrote \u201cI would now like to call the world\u2019s attention to the moment where Normani bounces a basketball off of her ass. This occurs right around the 1:54 mark of the new \u201cMotivation\u201d video, and it is honestly an astonishing physical feat, some strip-club [[Jackie Chan]] shit. The rest of the video is good. That one brief dance move is instantly iconic, like the [[Michael Jackson]] \u201c[[Smooth Criminal]]\u201d lean.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2055111/the-5-best-videos-of-the-week-382/franchises/straight-to-video/|title=The 5 Best Videos Of The Week|date=2019-08-16|website=Stereogum|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> ''Dee Lockett'' of [[Vulture magazine|Vulture]] wrote \u201cFor her debut solo single, Normani did what she came to do. A (destiny\u2019s) child of the 2000s raised on a steady diet of 106 & Park, \u201cCrazy in Love,\u201d \u201cGoodies,\u201d Omarian, and J.Lo circa the \u201cI\u2019m Real\u201d remix, Normani bottled all those influences, injected them into her veins, and said, \u201cYes, A star is born.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/08/doja-cat-normani-rosalia-won-the-week-in-music-videos.html|title=Doja Cat, Normani, and Rosal\u00eda Casually Won the Week in Music Videos|last=Lockett|first=Dee|date=2019-08-16|website=Vulture|language=en-us|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref>\n\n[[E! News]] listed the music video for the song among the pop culture moments that defined 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1101525/every-single-pop-culture-moment-that-defined-2019|title=Every Single Pop Culture Moment That Defined 2019|date=December 11, 2019|website=E! Online|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-09}}</ref> [[Vibe (magazine)|''Vibe'']] named \u201cMotivation\u201d as the best music video of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vibe.com/photos/25-best-music-videos-of-2019/khaled-higher_kouced-1576110990|title=25 Best Music Videos Of 2019|date=2019-12-31|website=Vibe|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> [[Pitchfork (website)|''Pitchfork'']] named the music video as the 2nd best of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/best-music-videos-2019/|title=The 20 Best Music Videos of 2019|last=Pitchfork|website=Pitchfork|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> It was voted Best Music Video in the 2019 [[Popjustice]] Readers' Poll.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popjustice.com/articles/the-2019-popjustice-readers-poll/|title=The 2019 Popjustice Readers' Poll: THE RESULTS! \u2022 Popjustice|date=2019-12-23|website=Popjustice|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' included the music video in its list for Best Music Videos of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-music-videos-2019-928435/|title=The 25 Best Music Videos of 2019|last=Shaffer|first=Claire|last2=Shaffer|first2=Claire|date=2019-12-19|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> [[Insider Inc.|''Insider'']] ranked the music video as the 6th Best of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insider.com/best-music-videos-this-year-ranked-2019-8|title=The 57 best music videos of 2019, ranked|last=Ahlgrim|first=Callie|website=Insider|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> ''[[Slant Magazine]]'' ranked it among its 20 best music videos of 2019, with ''Sophia Ordaz'' saying that \u201cMotivation\u201d captures the potential Normani has to become the next unstoppable female entertainer, emulating the showmanship of such pop icons as [[Janet Jackson]], [[Britney Spears]]'','' and [[Beyonc\u00e9]].\u201d<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/the-20-best-music-videos-of-2019/|title=The 20 Best Music Videos of 2019|last=Staff|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> [[PopSugar|''Popsugar'']] named \u201cMotivation\u201d as one of the Sexiest Videos of the 2010s,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popsugar.com.au/node/46982584|title=65 of This Decade's Sexiest Music Videos That'll Get You Hot and Bothered|last=Nguyen|first=Stacey|date=2019-12-06|website=POPSUGAR Celebrity Australia|language=en-AU|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> and as one of the Best Dance Videos of the 2010s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popsugar.co.uk/node/47014532|title=75 of the Decade's Most Mesmerising Music Video Dances|last=Cubit|first=Brea|date=2019-12-13|website=POPSUGAR Entertainment UK|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> Wonderland Magazine named it one of the 7 Best Music Videos of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wonderlandmagazine.com/2019/11/21/best-music-videos-2019-harry-styles-solange/|title=From Solange to Harry Styles: All The Best Music Videos Of 2019|date=2019-11-21|website=Wonderland|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> [[Idolator (website)|''Idolator'']] named the music video the 2nd Best of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7905274/from-motivation-to-small-talk-the-55-best-music-videos-of-2019|title=From &#8220;Motivation&#8221; To &#8220;Small Talk,&#8221; The 55 Best Music Videos Of 2019|date=2020-01-09|website=idolator|access-date=2020-01-09}}</ref> [[Shondaland]] named \u201cMotivation\u201d as one of the 10 Best Music Videos of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.shondaland.com/live/a30141930/the-10-best-music-videos-from-2019/|title=The 10 Best Music Videos from 2019|last=Tamola|first=Katie|date=2019-12-11|website=Shondaland|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-09}}</ref>\n\nSeveral publications including [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/columns/hip-hop/8529523/saweetie-stylist-sankara-performance-fashion-outfits|title=Saweetie & Her Stylist On Their Performance Outfits {{!}} Billboard|date=2019-09-10|website=www.billboard.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref> [[Paper (magazine)|Paper Magazine]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/nostalgic-2000s-fashion-2639942048.html?rebelltitem=2#rebelltitem2?rebelltitem=2|title=Why Everyone Is Referencing the Early Aughts|date=2019-08-21|website=PAPER|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref> [[The New York Times]]<ref>{{Cite news|last=Zoladz|first=Lindsay|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/26/arts/music/y2k-trl-pop-music.html|title=For Pop Stars in Their 20s, It\u2019s Totally the \u201990s All Over Again|date=2020-04-26|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-27|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> and [[Genius (website)|Genius]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/how-saweetie-tory-lanez-normani-more-are-bringing-back-the-2000s-hits-of-their-childhood|title=How Saweetie, Tory Lanez, Normani, & More Are Bringing Back The 2000s Hits Of Their Childhood|website=Genius|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref> noted \"Motivation\" for being among the music videos following a larger cultural trend of [[2000s (decade)|early-'00s]] nostalgia. [[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]] listed it as one of the best choreography-centric videos of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/music/a28862869/best-choreography-music-videos-2019/|title=Music Videos With Perfect Choreography Are Finally Back: Here\u2019s How to Learn the Dances|website=Cosmopolitan|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\n[[File:Dangerous Woman Tour in Manchester4.jpg|thumb|right|[[Ariana Grande]] (pictured in February 2017) co-wrote \"Motivation\".]]\n''[[Forbes]]'' wrote that \"Motivation\" \"sounds like the perfectly-crafted pop song [...] catchy, summery and fun\", adding that it is reminiscent of co-writer [[Ariana Grande]]'s sound, and while familiar, it \"provides something currently missing from the pop landscape.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2019/08/16/normani-returns-with-new-single-motivation-co-written-with-ariana-grande/#37a61e1b47e7|title=Normani Returns With New Single 'Motivation,' Co-Written With Ariana Grande|work=Forbes|date=August 16, 2019|accessdate=August 16, 2019|first=Hugh|last=McIntyre}}</ref> ''[[i-D]]'' said the song is a \"smash\" with a catchy chorus, and it recalls the \"Rich Harrison-produced pop of the early 2000s\" and [[Beyonc\u00e9]]'s [[Beyonc\u00e9 2018 Coachella performance|Coachella performance]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_uk/article/a35daz/00s-music-videos-normani-motivation|title=all the iconic 00s music videos referenced in normani's \"motivation\"|work=[[i-D]]|date=August 16, 2019|accessdate=August 16, 2019|first=Alim|last=Kheraj}}</ref> ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' named it \"Best New Track\", saying Normani's \"sultry, syncopated vocal lines bear the imprint of co-writer Ariana Grande\", and she \"seems to draw on both \"Check On It\"-era Beyonc\u00e9 and the brassy sounds of ''[[Homecoming (2019 film)|Homecoming]]''.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title=\"Motivation\" by Normani review|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/normani-motivation/|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=August 16, 2019|accessdate=August 16, 2019|first=Michelle|last=Kim}}</ref> ''[[The Guardian]]'' described the song as a \"buoyant, horn-laced, late-summer BBQ bop that nestles in the nook between Ariana Grande and 2006-era Beyonc\u00e9.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/aug/16/tracks-of-the-week-reviewed-normani-katy-perry-lana-del-rey|title=Tracks of the week reviewed: Normani, Katy Perry, Lana Del Rey|last=Cragg|first=Michael|date=August 16, 2019|work=The Guardian|accessdate=August 16, 2019|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' considered the track a \"sticky bop perfectly primed to get us through the rest of the summer\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/music/story/2019-08-16/normani-motivation-fifth-harmony-video-beyonce|title=Relive the rush of 'Crazy in Love'-era Beyonc\u00e9 with Normani's new video, 'Motivation'|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=August 16, 2019|accessdate=August 19, 2019|first=Gerrick|last=Kennedy}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' called the song when you can \"actually hear a pop superstar be[ing] born.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/song-you-need-to-know-normani-motivation-new-single-872129/|title=Song You Need to Know: Normani, 'Motivation'|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|date=August 21, 2019|work=Rolling Stone|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=August 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Recognition ===\n[[Time (magazine)|TIME]] ranked \u201cMotivation\u201d 2nd on their list of the 50 Best Workout Songs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/5502429/best-workout-songs/|title=The 50 of the Best Workout Songs to Motivate You|last=January 8|first=Raisa Bruner|last2=2020|website=Time|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> The song was ranked 79th on the top 100 songs of the 2010s by ''[[Crack Magazine]]'', which described it as a \"superlatively bright, bouncy bop that is steeped in a knowledge of pop and R&B history, but which also feels like the start of something wonderful.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://crackmagazine.net/article/what-just-happened/the-top-100-songs-of-the-decade/|title=The top 100 songs of the decade|website=Crack Magazine|access-date=2019-11-14}}</ref> [[The New York Times]] ranked it 13th on their 2020 list of 25 Songs That Matter Now.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/03/11/magazine/best-songs.html|title=25 Songs That Matter Now|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-03-12|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]'' included the song in its list of the 28 Best R&B Songs of Summer 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/ywankj/best-r-and-b-songs-and-albums-of-summer-2019|title=The 28 Best R&B Songs of Summer 2019|last=Corry|first=Hunter French,Kristin|date=2019-09-27|website=Vice|language=en|access-date=2019-11-07}}</ref> ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'' named \"Motivation\" as the best \"banger\" of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/music/g25833832/best-new-songs-2019/|title=These 19 New Songs Are the Best Bangers of 2019|last=Chambers|first=Hannah|last2=Baker|first2=Emma|date=2019-11-20|website=Cosmopolitan|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-23}}</ref> [[PopBuzz]] named it the Best Song of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popbuzz.com/music/features/best-singles-2019-songs-of-the-year/|title=The 20 best singles of 2019|website=PopBuzz|language=en|access-date=2019-12-12}}</ref> [[Uproxx]] and ''[[The Guardian]]'' also included the song in their Best Songs of 2019 list, at 13th and 17th respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/music/best-songs-of-2019-ranked/|title=The 50 Best Songs Of 2019|date=2019-12-03|website=UPROXX|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/dec/02/the-20-best-songs-of-2019-tracks|title=The 20 best songs of 2019|last=Beaumont-Thomas|first=Ben|date=2019-12-02|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-12-03|last2=Snapes|first2=Laura|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> [[Instinct (magazine)|''Instinct'']] magazine named it the tenth Top Female Bop of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://instinctmagazine.com/what-are-the-top-10-female-bops-of-2019/|title=What Are The Top 10 Female Bops of 2019?|last=http://#|date=2019-12-05|website=Instinct Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-05}}</ref> [[Associated Press]] ranked \"Motivation\" as the 10th best song of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/d9702da525ab0384227df4bb61634f34|title=AP's top songs of 2019: Jhene Aiko, Sam Smith, Normani|date=2019-12-06|website=AP NEWS|access-date=2019-12-06}}</ref> ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' ranked it at number 14 among their 100 Best Songs of 2019 list, saying that Normani \"breezed through the track, with the confidence of an artist who knows her worth, and further stamped her star power with the stunningly gymnastic choreography in its video. Both song and video contain the brassy essence of pop R&B's early-2000s glory days, an innocent coquettishness and pure joy in hitting the dance floor\u2014and in paying homage to that era, Normani hit a hard reset on her career trajectory, proving that she was always more formidable than she'd gotten credit for.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/best-songs-2019/|title=The 100 Best Songs of 2019|last=Nast|first=Cond\u00e9|website=Pitchfork|language=en|access-date=2019-12-09}}</ref> ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' ranked \"Motivation\" as the 27th Best Song of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8545893/best-songs-of-2019-top-100|title=The 100 Best Songs of 2019: Staff List|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> ''[[British GQ]]'' ranked it as the second best song of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/culture/article/best-songs-2019|title=The biggest, boldest songs of 2019|website=British GQ|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref> \"Motivation\" was also included in the Best Songs of 2019 list for ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'', ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]'', ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'', ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/music/2019/12/20/best-songs-of-2019/|title=The best songs of 2019|website=EW.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/akwwxz/the-100-best-songs-of-2019|title=The 100 Best Songs of 2019|last=Staff|first=Alex Jenkins,VICE|date=2019-12-18|website=Vice|language=en|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/music/g25939887/best-songs-2019/|title=The 60 Best Songs of 2019|last=ELLE.com|date=2019-12-23|website=ELLE|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/best-songs-2019|title=The 34 Best Songs of 2019|last=Specter|first=Emma|website=Vogue|language=en|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref> [[iHeartRadio]] placed the song among 140 songs that defined the 2010s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-12-06-140-songs-that-defined-the-2010s/|website=www.iheart.com|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\n== Live performances ==\nNormani first performed \"Motivation\" at the [[2019 MTV Video Music Awards]] on August 26, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2019/08/normani-performs-motivation-vmas-2019/\n|title=Watch Normani Perform 'Motivation' at the 2019 VMAs|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|date=August 26, 2019|accessdate=August 27, 2019}}</ref> The performance was positively-received.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a28799936/normani-performance-vma-2019/|title=Normani Gave the Performance of the Year at the 2019 VMAs|last=Gonzales|first=Erica|date=August 27, 2019|website=[[Harper's BAZAAR]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=December 30, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8528413/normani-2019-mtv-vmas-performance-motivation-video|title=Normani Brings Epic Choreo, Stunning Vocals to 'Motivation' Performance at the 2019 MTV VMAs: Watch|last=Payne|first=Chris|date=August 26, 2019|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=December 30, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/normani-motivatino-mtv-video-music-awards-875604/|title=Watch Normani Hold Court With 'Motivation' at MTV VMAs|last=Leight|first=Elias|date=August 27, 2019|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=December 30, 2019|last2=Blistein|first2=Jon}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2019\n|[[Soul Train Music Awards]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8540527/soul-train-awards-2019-nominations-list|title=Chris Brown, Drake, Beyonc\u00e9 and Lizzo Top Nominees For 2019 Soul Train Awards: Exclusive|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-10-25}}</ref>\n|[[Soul Train Music Award for Best Dance Performance|Best Dance Performance]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n|W Magazine Award<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/song-of-summer-2019|title=The Song of the Summer 2019 Awards|last=Marine|first=Brooke|website=W Magazine|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref>\n|Song of The Summer That Was Released Too Late\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n|Dance Magazine Awards<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dancemagazine.com/readers-choice-2019-2641560590.html|title=These Are the Dance Moments Our Readers Loved the Most This Year|date=2019-12-10|website=Dance Magazine|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</r