ww.standard.co.uk/stayingin/winter-love-island/2020-music-songs-tracklist-covers-a4332981.html|title=Every song that features in 2020's Winter Love Island series|date=2020-01-21|website=Evening Standard|language=en|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref> The song was also featured in the [[Pandora Radio]] TV commercial, 'Be You: Afternoon'(2019).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ispot.tv/ad/Z2u0/pandora-radio-be-you-afternoon-song-by-normani|title=Pandora Radio TV Commercial, 'Be You: Afternoon' Song by Normani|website=iSpot.tv|language=en|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref> [[Jeff Goldblum]] went viral after he performed an impromptu dance performance at an LGBTQ New Orleans Pride Parade while taping an episode of his [[National Geographic]] show [[The World According to Jeff Goldblum]] for [[Disney+]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8529045/jeff-goldblum-dancing-normani-motivation-video|title=This Video Of Jeff Goldblum Dancing to Normani's 'Motivation' Is the Best Thing You'll See Today|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/jeff-goldblum-dancing-normani-apos-214922357.html|title=Jeff Goldblum Dancing to Normani's 'Motivation' Will Make Your Day -- Watch!|website=news.yahoo.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref> [[Stephen \"tWitch\" Boss]] and his then pregnant wife [[Allison Holker]] performed a dance routine to \u201cMotivation\u201d as part of his guest hosting gig for [[The Ellen Show]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.eonline.com/amp/news/1082119/stephen-twitch-boss-and-allison-holker-will-give-you-the-motivation-to-get-up-and-dance|title=Stephen ''tWitch'' Boss & Allison Holker Give Motivation to Dance {{!}} E! News|website=m.eonline.com|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>\n== Credits and personnel ==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/115381522/track/115381523|title=Try the TIDAL Web Player|website=listen.tidal.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-18}}</ref>\n\n* [[Normani]] \u2013 vocals, songwriter\n* [[Ariana Grande]] \u2013 songwriter\n* [[Max Martin]] \u2013 songwriter\n* [[Savan Kotecha]] \u2013 songwriter, backing vocals\n* [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]] \u2013 producer, songwriter, programmer, vocal producer, backing vocals, bass, drums, keyboards\n* [[Kuk Harrell]] \u2013 vocal producer\n* [[Carolina Liar|Peter Carlsson]] \u2013 vocal producer\n* Simone Torres \u2013 vocal producer\n* Daniel Oestreicher \u2013 baritone saxophone\n* Troy \"Trombone Shorty\" Andrews \u2013 trumpet, trombone\n* Cory Bice \u2013 engineer\n* Jeremy Lertola \u2013 engineer\n* John Hanes \u2013 engineer\n* Sam Holland \u2013 engineer\n* Serban Ghenea \u2013 mixing engineer\n* Dave Kutch \u2013 mastering engineer\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|28|artist=Normani|song=Motivation|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 7, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|40|artist=Normani|song=Motivation|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 4, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|24|artist=Normani Kordei|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 27, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardcanadachrtop40|11|artist=Normani Kordei|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardcanadahotac|29|artist=Normani Kordei|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| Colombia ([[National-Report]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://national-report.com/top-colombia/|title=Top 100 Colombia}}</ref>\n| 73\n|- \n! scope=\"row\"| Croatia ([[Croatian Radiotelevision|HRT]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://radio.hrt.hr/clanak/arc-100-datum-23-rujna-2019/209085/|title=Croatia ARC TOP 100|publisher=HRT|accessdate=September 27, 2019}}</ref>\n| 84\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| France Downloads ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snepmusique.co